# SpanSaver — always-on context

Hackathon project (Agents of SigNoz, deadline July 26, 2026). SpanSaver is an AI auditor that
finds money leaking in two domains — telemetry ingested into SigNoz that no dashboard/alert
uses, and LLM token waste mined from gen_ai spans — then generates the fix, applies it, and
verifies savings with real metrics. Loop: Detect → Prove safety → Fix → Apply → Verify.

Team is 1 human + AI. Judges are 30+ yr US engineers. A working, verified demo beats elegant
architecture every time.

## Non-negotiables
- **Introspect, don't guess.** SigNoz API routes, ClickHouse table names, and span attribute
  keys vary by version. Verify against the live system (SHOW TABLES, DESCRIBE, real API
  responses, one dumped span) before writing queries. Never invent endpoints or schemas.
- **No fabricated numbers.** Every figure in the UI comes from a real query. Only pricing
  rates are assumptions; they live in `.env` and render with an "assumed rate" label.
- **Findings need evidence.** Each leak finding must include ≥1 working deep-link into the
  SigNoz UI. No link → not done.
- **Patches are additive files** in `collector/patches/` with a header comment (finding id +
  timestamp). Never mutate the baseline collector config at runtime.
- **Env for everything** — URLs, keys, ports, prices. No hardcoding.
- **After July 24:** small diffs only, no refactors of working code, no new deps without
  asking.
- **Fail loud** with actionable error messages; silent empty states are bugs.

## Spec source of truth
`docs/LEAK-CATALOG.md` defines every leak type (detection, $ math, fix, safety proof,
verification). Implement against it; update it if reality forces a change.

## Definition of done
Runs via a make target, visible in UI or SigNoz, one line in README, human saw it work.
